# Student Connect ‚Äî Cursor Rules

You are working on a party and event discovery web app for people aged 14‚Äì25. Hosts create public or private events; guests discover and RSVP. V1 MVP deadline: July 2026.

## Stack (do not deviate)

- Next.js 14, App Router only ‚Äî never Pages Router
- TypeScript strict mode ‚Äî never use `any`
- Supabase (Postgres) for database and auth via `@supabase/ssr`
- Tailwind CSS for styling
- Default to Server Components; add `"use client"` only when needed
- `createServerClient` in server components and API routes
- `createBrowserClient` in client components
- Write RLS policies for every table
- Never expose `SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY` on the client
- Regenerate types after schema changes: `supabase gen types typescript`

## Never suggest or introduce

Prisma, Firebase, PlanetScale, Clerk, NextAuth, React Router, Redux, Zustand, Pages Router patterns, or `any` in TypeScript.

## Project layout

- `app/` ‚Äî routes (`app/e/[invite_code]/` is the public shareable event page)
- `components/` ‚Äî shared UI
- `lib/` ‚Äî Supabase clients and utilities
- `types/` ‚Äî generated Supabase types and custom types
- `features/` ‚Äî feature modules (auth, explore, etc.)
- `party-app/SCHEMA.md` ‚Äî full data model reference

## Data model (essentials)

Tables: `profiles`, `events`, `rsvps`, `tasks` (stubbed), `votes` (stubbed).

- `events.visibility`: `'public' | 'private'`
- `events.invite_code`: short random string for `/e/[invite_code]` links
- `rsvps.status`: `'going' | 'not_going'`
- `profiles.party_score`: integer, starts at 0 (V2 only ‚Äî do not build UI for it)

## V1 scope ‚Äî build only these

- Email sign up / log in
- Profile: display name, initials avatar, age
- Explore page: all public events, newest first
  - Non-users: event name, type, date, location only ‚Äî no attendee names or RSVP
  - Signed-in users: full details and RSVP
- Create event: name, description, type, date, time, location
- Event visibility: public (explore) or private (link only)
- RSVP: going / not going
- Host guest list: attendee names, ages, total headcount
- Shareable link at `/e/[invite_code]` ‚Äî basic info visible without auth; prompt to sign up for more
- Mobile responsive

## Out of V1 ‚Äî do not implement or suggest

Profile photo upload, gender field, age limits on events, join-request/approval flow, collaborative events, voting, party score/reputation UI, discovery filters, external share buttons (WhatsApp/Instagram), checklist/who-brings-what, push notifications, PWA, native app, AI features, payments, public profile pages, party type tags.

## Environment variables

Read from `process.env` ‚Äî never hardcode:

- `NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL`
- `NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY`
- `SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY` (server only)

## Current state

Auth is complete. Supabase is connected. `middleware.ts` is in place.

**Next task:** onboarding flow ‚Äî full name, age, and initials avatar.

## When coding

- Match existing patterns in the file you are editing
- Keep diffs minimal and scoped to the request
- Do not add features outside V1 scope
- Do not create commits unless explicitly asked
